cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

The paper deals with image classification using a novel supervised learning method based on self-paced learning (SPL) and support vector machines (SVM). The paper focuses on polarimetric synthetic aperture radar (PolSAR) image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of SPL and SVM also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of neighborhood constraints, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI).
